    <!-- pure grid group -->
    <div class="pure-g">
      <div class="pure-u-1-2">
        <div class="description description-right">
          <h2>Trends across Genders</h2>
          <p>One interesting trend is that bullying rates have decreased across the years in all regions and genders. Of
            note
            is that the bullying rate in boys is now 1.9% lower than that in girls, despite starting 2.2% higher. This
            change
            occurred between 2010 and 2011. We speculate that this may be due to the popularisation of social media
            around this
            time, allowing for different avenues of bullying, such as cyberbullying, to emerge. </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
    <!-- end pure grid group -->

    <!-- pure grid group -->
    <div class="pure-g">
